                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/twowheeler/upcomming/2025/honda cbr500r/red.webp" alt="red" title="red" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>At the heart of the CBR500R's appeal lies its engine—a robust, reliable, and perfectly balanced power unit that has earned a reputation for being one of the best middleweight twins on the market.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">The Heart of the Beast: 471cc Parallel-Twin Engine</span></p>
                <p>The 2025 model continues to be powered by Honda's celebrated 471cc liquid-cooled, DOHC, parallel-twin engine. This engine is designed for a perfect balance of performance and accessibility, making it ideal for both seasoned riders and those graduating from lower-capacity machines.</p>
                <p>While the fundamental engine architecture remains trusted, Honda has made subtle but significant updates to the ECU tuning for the 2025 model. The result is an improved "acceleration feel," particularly in the low and mid-range, where most real-world riding takes place. The engine delivers a punchy and usable performance that’s never intimidating.</p><div style="overflow-x: auto;">

