                <p>The engine’s smooth and refined power delivery is a hallmark of Honda engineering. The parallel-twin configuration provides a delightful exhaust note without the harsh vibrations often associated with single-cylinder units, ensuring a comfortable and enjoyable ride, whether you're commuting or attacking a winding mountain road.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Clutch and Gearbox: Seamless Shifting</span></p>
                <p>To complement the retuned engine, the CBR500R features a slick 6-speed manual transmission, coupled with an <span class="font-weight-700">Assist and Slipper Clutch. </span>This is a game-changing feature, especially for a bike in this class.</p>
                <p>The <span class="font-weight-700">Assist function </span>reduces the lever effort required to pull the clutch, making city riding and stop-and-go traffic far less tiring. The<span class="font-weight-700"> Slipper function </span>prevents the rear wheel from hopping or locking up under aggressive downshifts, providing stability and confidence when braking hard before a corner. This technology elevates the riding experience, making it safer and significantly more intuitive for newer riders.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage and Range</span></p>
                <p>Despite its sporty credentials, the CBR500R is known for being surprisingly frugal. With an mileage of around <span class="font-weight-700">25-28 km/l </span>(WMTC cycle), it offers a fantastic range. Paired with a generous <span class="font-weight-700">17.1-litre fuel tank, </span>riders can easily achieve a range of over 450 km on a single tank, making it a stellar choice for long-distance touring without the constant worry of searching for a fuel station. This excellent fuel efficiency, combined with Honda’s renowned reliability, truly makes the CBR500R a practical machine for daily use and weekend adventures.</p>
