                </div>
                <p>The 2025 iteration of the<span class="font-weight-700"> CBR500R </span>receives a significant technological overhaul to keep it competitive with the latest generation of rivals. The biggest highlight is the completely redesigned instrument cluster and the addition of crucial electronic rider aids.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Connectivity and Instrumentation</span></p>
                <p>Replacing the older LCD unit is a stunning<span class="font-weight-700"> 5-inch Full-Colour TFT Display. </span>This modern, high-resolution screen offers exceptional clarity and brightness, even in direct sunlight. It displays all the critical information—speed, tachometer, fuel gauge, odometer, trip meters, and a much-requested<span class="font-weight-700"> Gear Position Indicator</span>—with a customizable layout.</p>
                <p>Crucially, the new TFT screen offers connectivity via the<span class="font-weight-700"> Honda RoadSync</span> application. This Bluetooth-based system allows the rider to manage phone calls, text messages, music playback, and even turn-by-turn navigation (where available) directly from the bike's handlebar controls, minimizing distractions and enhancing the overall ride experience.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Electronic Rider Aids: Safety Firs</span>t</p>
                <p>For the first time, the CBR500R is to include<span class="font-weight-700"> Honda Selectable Torque Control (HSTC) </span>as a standard feature. HSTC is Honda’s sophisticated traction control system, which monitors the difference in speed between the front and rear wheels. If it detects a slip, it instantly modulates engine power to regain traction. This is an invaluable safety net, especially when accelerating on slippery surfaces like wet asphalt or gravel.</p>
                <p>Another feature enhancing safety is the<span class="font-weight-700"> Emergency Stop Signal (ESS).</span> This system detects sudden, aggressive braking and automatically flashes the hazard lights to warn following vehicles, significantly reducing the risk of a rear-end collision.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Comfort and Convenience Features</span></p>
